# StoryForge Development Roadmap

> **Vision:** Build a self-hosted, extensible tabletop RPG campaign manager where the Core Engine is game-agnostic and individual RPG systems (VTM, Call of Cthulhu, D&D, etc.) are implemented as plugins.

---

# Guiding Principles

* Deliver vertical slices instead of isolated backend/frontend work.
* Every sprint should produce a usable application.
* The Core Engine never contains game-specific rules.
* Plugins extend the engine without modifying it.
* Business logic belongs in services, not GraphQL resolvers or React components.

---

# Sprint 0 — Project Foundation ✅

## Goal

Establish a production-ready development environment.

### Deliverables

* pnpm Workspace
* Turborepo
* React + Vite frontend
* Fastify backend
* GraphQL setup
* Shared packages
* Docker skeleton
* Git repository
* TypeScript
* ESLint
* Prettier
* Husky
* CI skeleton

### Definition of Done

Developers can run:

```bash
pnpm install
pnpm dev
```

and start both frontend and backend locally.

